FBIS4-60234 "drnes099_l_94001" FBIS-NES-94-099 Daily Report 21 May 1994 ISRAEL Leaders, Others Comment on Capture of al-Dirani Leaders, Others Comment on Capture of al-Dirani Radio Reports IDF Operation TA2105043694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0405 GMT 21 May 94 TA2105043694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Last night, an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] force operating deep in Lebanon's al-Biqa' region captured and brought to Israel Mustafa al-Dirani, the head of a radical terrorist organization which took navigator Ron Arad captive in 1986. Al-Dirani heads an organization called the Believer's Resistance. An IDF spokesman reported that all our forces returned safely to base. A REUTERS reporter in al-Biqa' reported that an IDF force flew by helicopter to al-Dirani's village of (al-Qassanabah), which is located 10 kilometers from Zahlah. The commando force kidnapped al-Dirani from his home. IDF representatives have informed the Arad family about the operation.
